_

#motivationalspeaker #selfimprovement #mystory #lifechanging #gratitude #gratitudeattitude #lifestory #keynotespeaker

On this day 10 years ago, I stepped into a car not knowing that 10 minutes later I would get into a traumatic accident that almost stole my life.

I also didn’t know it would shape my entire life’s work and be the fuel for my message. 

When things happen to us, we always have the choice between letting it serve us negatively or positively. My invitation to you is never forget that choice is always available to you ♥️

YOU changed my entire life 2 years ago 🫶🏻

I’m sitting at my kitchen table as I write this. The same exact place I was sitting 2 years ago today when I officially released my book, You Deserve This Sh!t. I was nervous, excited, overwhelmed, and everything in between. I didn’t really think much would come from this. I thought it would be another forgotten self-help book.

But I was wrong. Right when I was about to give up on the book (6 months after the release), the universe placed it right on center stage in the spotlight. To my surprise, people started buying it every single day. Since then, the book has gone on to sell over 25,000 copies and amass close to 600 reviews on Amazon.

I feel so incredibly grateful to be on a path of service and impact. But to be completely honest, none of this would be possible without you and your unconditional support.

YOU made this a global bestseller. YOU changed my life. YOU did this.

I am so so deeply appreciative for you showing up, supporting this book, and spreading the word. From the deepest part of my soul, thank you 🫶🏻

#booktok #bookrecommendations #bookreviewer #selfimprovement #personalgrowth #personaldevelopment #selfdevelopment #selfhelp #selfhelpbooks #findyourpath #bookrecs

This book is just the beginning. Can’t wait to see what’s next :)

Nicolle and I have been in a healthy relationship for a solid 6 years (getting married in less than 3 months!!!).

One thing that has been a constant since the very beginning that we both agree has helped us build a healthy relationship is communication.

It’s really hard to know how to support you partner if you don’t ask how they’re feeling / what they need. On the flip side, it’s also really hard to receive the support you need if you don’t express how you’re feeling / what you need.

After a long, tough day, these are some questions that help us support one another / receive the support we need most.

What questions are we missing? ♥️

I’ve always been someone to show love through my thoughtfulness and acts of service. This has been at the center of mine and Nicolle’s relationship since it all started about six years ago and is something we both cherish :)

I’ve never shared this with anyone 🤍

The other day I was talking with a friend about my car accident 10 years ago, and that’s when this fear came to the surface. It hit me like a train and made me feel really emotional.

But I’m learning everything in life serves us, even our fears. For me, the fear of regretting the last words I said to someone I love has made me act more carefully and intentionally with those people. I will do anything to make sure my last words are “I love you” instead of regretting being upset at them for something so insignificant and silly.

While I don’t wish losing a loved one upon anyone, it’s something we’ll all face inevitably, and sometimes unexpectedly. This means we may not know when our last moments, words, and hugs will be. So I wanted to share this with you to help you create a small shift that changes how you end conversations or nights with your loved ones.

All I want is for you to cherish the last moments, words, and hugs you have with a loved one instead of regret them and feel guilty.

Sending you love and strength 🤍

_

10 journal prompts that reveal what’s blocking your light ✨

I’ve been journaling consistently since 2016, which has helped me reveal my magic and light—the fullest version of myself. It’s the one thing I recommend everyone does. These prompts can help you get started:

1. What are 3-5 things I do consistently that deplete my energy?

2. What’s causing my frustration, and what shift is the universe calling on me to make to relieve that frustration?

3. If I had to change one thing about my life today that’s dimming my light, what would I change?

4. What relationships or people in my life are holding me back from stepping into my true self?

5. If I had to describe my “light” in one paragraph, what would I say? Where in my life am I not aligned with that description?

📖 If you want to shed darkness and step into your light + align with your calling, I created a book + workbook, which includes exercises + daily journal prompts, to help you find your purpose in 30 days. You can get 50% off through the link in my bio 🤍

6. What activities am I still doing that no longer serve my greatest and highest good?

7. Can I identify any content or media I’m consuming that’s making me have a negative outlook?

8. What are 3-5 habits that are pulling me away from how I want to show up, and which habit can I break today?

9. What do I need to release and let go of that is making me believe I’m somebody who I’m not?

10. Do I have any recurring patterns that pull me away from what I know is best for my personal journey?

💡You can also get 100 free journal prompts through the link in my bio 💡

The secret to journaling is finding a type of writing or prompt that you enjoy. So while there are 10 journal prompts, choose the ones that you feel most drawn to. They’ll all guide you in the right direction :)

5 books to shed darkness, step into your light, and align with your calling ✨

Don’t aim to read a certain number of books per year. Instead, aim to integrate what you learn into your life before picking up a new book. We want progress, not paralysis by information overload.

These are 5 books that have given my life so much light:

1. The Surrender Experiment by Michael A. Singer: This was legit one of the first books where I said, “that book changed my life.” It expanded my perspective and revealed the power of trusting the flow of the universe.

2. Untethered Soul by Michael A. Singer: This is the perfect follow-up book for The Surrender Experiment. This book taught me how to let go and soar beyond my own limitations.

3. You Deserve This Sh!t by me: For most of my life, finding my path felt impossible. I wanted to give up. But I didn’t, and I eventually found my calling. This book reveals the step-by-step process I went through to overcome those challenges.

4. Experiential Billionaire by Bridget Hilton and Joe Huff: This is a newer one for me, but it packs a punch. It’s easy to think we have all the time in the world to live our life, but the clock ticks every day. This book put me on a path of no regrets.

5. The Mountain Is You by Brianna Wiest: I didn’t even know I was sabotaging myself until I read this. This book helped me turn that self-sabotage into self-mastery.

There’s no correct order to read these books. Read the ones that call your name. If you start to one but don’t connect with it, set it down and pick a new one.

The number of books you read doesn’t matter but what you integrate does ❤️

_

The secret that changed my life ❤️

10 journal prompts to escape feeling paralyzed and create possibilities 💫

I picked up journaling in 2016 to document my solo backpacking trip. I didn’t know it was going to become a life-long practice that made me more self-aware and, as a result, opened me up to possibilities that feel incredibly aligned.

If that sounds like something you want to experience, you can get started with these prompts:

1. What is one small shift I can make today to show up as a better person tomorrow?

2. When I think about the dream version of myself, what opportunities do they attract? What am I doing that’s blocking me from attracting those opportunities now?

3. How would my life feel if I focused on living with an open heart and an open mind that aligned me with love instead of fear?

4. What are three simple activities that pour joy into my life, and how can I do more of them?

5. Can I identify any recurring patterns that don’t align with the person I want to become or the life I want to live?

💡If you’re ready to step into your light and align with your calling, I created a free 7-day journaling challenge so you settle into your own personal groove. You can sign up through the link in my bio (I also have 100 free journal prompts there too)💡

6. What would happen if I poured more intention and purpose into my choices and decisions?

7. Where do I feel most held back in my life, and could I free myself by giving more attention to those areas?

8. What feels like a bigger risk, remaining the same or taking ownership of my life?

9. When I think about venturing outside my comfort zone, how does that make me feel, and what shifts do I need to make to overcome any fears?

10. If my own child was in a similar situation as myself, how would I treat them, guide them, and support them?

I think the most beautiful part of journaling is the fact that every time you sit down to write, you are creating space to uncover more about yourself, and, therefore, uncovering more of your magic 🤍

Nobody talks about this part of changing your life 😳

Most people get change wrong by thinking taking action is the first step. However, the first step of change is self-awareness. Maybe it’s not the sexiest part of change, but when you develop your self-awareness, you give yourself a better chance at making changes that serve you best.

For the last 7 years, I’ve journaled to connect with myself and become more aware of where my life feels out of whack so I can make shifts that align me with a better life. It’s the one thing I recommend to everyone :)

If you want to add rocket fuel to your personal growth, use these journal prompts to unlock your inner world:

1. Identify 1-3 areas of your life where you feel frustration or tension. What do you think is causing those feelings? What is one small shift you can make in each area to alleviate the frustration or tension?

2. Imagine your ideal life (job, relationships, health, free time, hobbies, etc). What about your current life doesn’t align with this vision? What small shifts can you make to move one degree closer to the life you desire?

3. Write about a time in the last month where you felt present, connected to yourself, and at peace. What’s different about how you feel in this moment right now? What small shifts can you make over the next week to return to that positive state of mind?

4. If you could snap your finger and change one thing about your life immediately, what would you change? Now that you’re aware of this change, what’s one small shift you can make to start the process of change?

Choose the journal prompt that you feel the most drawn to and start there. If you want to keep going, by all means, do them all. It most definitely won’t hurt ❤️

If you skip number 3, you lose the game 🫡

I’ll admit that the new year can feel super overwhelming. All of a sudden you have to awake from your holiday slumber and get moving.

To make the beginning of the year feel easier, I simplify my annual preparation with these 3 steps:

1. REFLECT

- What do I need to let go of to step into the next version of myself?
- What challenges did I face and how they serve my greatest and highest good?
- What went well and why, and how can I do more of that in 2024?

2. VISUALIZE

Every year I write a letter to myself that covers all the things I want to accomplish in 2024. I write this in *past tense* as if I’ve already completed them and reflect on that letter at the end of the year.

3. PLAN

This is literally the most important step. If you skip this step, no progress will be made. Without a plan, your words are just a wish. But with a plan, your words are a promise.

I’m using a 12-week year (quarter goals, weekly action step) and @jesseitzler Big A## Calendar to plan out my 2024 and make it the most memorable year yet.
